# YouTube Transcript Analysis Implementation Plan

Enable agents (specifically Asan) to extract and analyze YouTube transcripts directly from URLs to provide rapid takeaways and research insights.

## Proposed Changes

### [Component] YouTube Transcript Tool

#### [NEW] [youtube.ts](file:///root/gravity-claw/src/tools/youtube.ts)
- Implement a `get_youtube_transcript` tool.
- Use a library or a scraping-based approach (like `youtube-transcript-api` equivalent in Node) to fetch transcripts without requiring a heavy official Data API key if possible.
- Fallback to metadata extraction if transcripts are disabled.

### [Component] Agent Loop Integration

#### [MODIFY] [loop.ts](file:///root/gravity-claw/src/agent/loop.ts)
- Register the `get_youtube_transcript` tool.
- Add execution logic in the tool loop.

#### [MODIFY] [index.ts](file:///root/gravity-claw/src/index.ts)
- Update Asan's system prompt to prioritize using the transcript tool when a YouTube link is received.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Test the `executeGetYoutubeTranscript` function with a known video URL.
- Verify the output is a readable text block.

### Manual Verification
- Send a YouTube link to Asan in Telegram and verify he uses the tool and provides takeaways.
